content: My progress has been okay, I guess. I've been able to clip in and out without too much trouble, but I still feel a bit awkward sometimes. I'm just not used to having my feet attached to the pedals, you know? I'm hoping with more practice, it'll become second nature. By the way, have you heard anything about the new bike path that's supposed to be built near the state park? I heard it's going to be a 12-mile trail that's perfect for road bikes like my Trek Emonda SL 6.
